### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

I want to use the rxResource-api which works pretty well when running the app. But writing tests for it is getting really in trouble. I spend some ours trying to figure out why this is not working, but did not found the issue. So maybe I am doing something wrong.

Here is my example.

I am creating a component with an rxResource. The rxResource is using a counter-Signal as an input and creating a text from it.

I would expect I could test the template from showing the calculated text. But I get the text value '' instead of "The counter is 100".

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'rx-resource-example',
  template: '<h1 id="text">{{ textResource.value() }}</h1>',
})
export class RxResourceExample {
  counter = signal(100);

  textResource = rxResource({
    request: () => {
      return this.counter();
    },
    loader: ({ request: counter }) => {
      console.log('Loading value with counter ' + counter);
      return of(`The counter is ${counter}`);
    },
  });
}

describe('Testing with rxResource', () => {
  async function setup() {
    await TestBed.configureTestingModule({
      imports: [RxResourceExample],
    }).compileComponents();
    const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(RxResourceExample);

    fixture.detectChanges();
    await fixture.whenStable();

    return { fixture };
  }

  it('should show text in the template', async () => {
    const { fixture } = await setup();

    expect(
      fixture.debugElement.query(By.css('#text')).nativeElement.textContent
    ).toEqual('The counter is 100');
  });
});

```

